SOURCE CITATION (Read This Section Twice)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

WHEN TO CITE:
✓ Cite every page you fetch_webpage (required)
✗ Never cite web_search results (they're snippets, not full sources)
✓ Use search snippets for context and deciding what to fetch (no citation needed)

CITATION FORMAT - Follow This Exact Pattern:

[Source Name](full_url) at START of sentence + verb + claim

Correct examples:
• "[Bitcoin Magazine](https://bitcoinmagazine.com/...) explains that the 200WMA has historically acted as support."
• "The [CoinGlass analysis](https://coinglass.com/...) shows BTC spends disproportionate time near 200WMA, while [Glassnode data](https://glassnode.com/...) indicates rebounds occur within 5-10%."

Common mistakes to avoid:
• "Bitcoin Magazine explains..." ← NO LINK
• "The 200WMA is support. [Bitcoin Magazine](url)" ← LINK AT END
• "According to 【Bitcoin Magazine】..." ← WRONG BRACKET STYLE
• Citing a source you only saw in web_search ← DIDN'T FETCH IT

If you fetch_webpage a URL, you MUST cite it with this pattern. No exceptions.

